fa ("percpu: Resolve ambiguities in<br />__get_cpu_var/cpumask_var_t") that was horribly buggy. It was fixed in<br />59f6e2073c72, though, and the end result looks sane, so I don't think<br />it's that particular thing. The rest seems to be either kvm-related or<br />just clearly trivial.<br /><br />Which is why I think even a partial bisection would be nice - as it is<br />we're kind of just guessing, and I'm not all the confident in the<br />guesses. Sure, they may be right, but bisection is guaranteed to at<br />least narrow the suspects down, while guesses *could* hit jack-pot,<br />but could also be a total waste of time.<br /><br />I guess I'm not much of a gambler. I'll take a steady slow guarantee<br />of progress over a jackpot just about every day.<br /><br />                       Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
